f=Product/PRODUCT-REDESIGN-PLAN.md · h1:Product Department Redesign Plan (v1 DRAFT)=**Status:** DRAFT discussion, approved, nothing built (rule 0.1) **Model directive:** any spawned sub-agents use **Fable**, never Opus **Owner:** CTO Product role **Supersedes:** catalog's 4-agent Product section (spec/ux/metric/loom, skills) see why. · h2:catalog structure insufficient=**No leader.** defect Agents had: four peers, law-writer. spec (Product Manager) natural head already orchestrates others' outputs PRDs backlog verdicts. **Nobody owns monetization.** Pricing research, packaging/tiers, price-change discipline appear nowhere 19-department catalog's product surface (Growth owns CAC/referrals, Finance owns treasury neither designs prices). business-running agents first-class gap: **price** department's missing agent. **Dangling pointer, again.** metric's protocol syncs definitions "river pipelines" river Data Analytics agent doesn't exist (the forge pattern repeated). Handled interface-shaped boundary now, binding department builds. **Rosters below house bar.** 2–3 skills agent Engineering/AI Agents' minimum Expanded agent splitting real protocol steps real skills, padding. **Rule-0.6 exposure.** Ellis 40% PMF bar, RICE weights, 5-user testing rounds, survey cadences rubrics/conventions. Kept suggested defaults, verdict flagged `reasoning-based, formula-verified` until logical layer gets real sources. **Genericization.** Strip `vyon-` prefixes; "per product/venture" becomes operator config (product profiles); NSM definitions, survey thresholds, tooling `<FILL_IN>`. **Experiment discipline already exists fleet.** proto's eval-first-design forge's benchmarking set house pattern (criteria frozen before building, blind scoring, verdicts recorded). loom reuses pattern product-side rather inventing rival one one discipline, three homes (design-time/release-time/run-time product-time). · h2:team agents pods=\| Pod \| Agent \| Role \| Core skills (custom C / marketplace M) \| · h2:team agents pods=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Definition** \| **spec** ⭐ \| Product Manager — writes the department's law \| prd-discipline (problem, evidence refs, explicit out-of-scope, quinn-testable acceptance criteria) C \· backlog-rules (evidence-gated intake, RICE w/ 0.6 flag, age-out) C \· opportunity-assessment (evidence-before-scoping: problem sizing, alternatives, do-nothing cost) C \· acceptance-criteria-handoff (the quinn bridge — echo-confirmed, edge's handoff pattern) C \· user-story-mapping M (candidate — search by purpose at build) \| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Discovery** \| **ux** \| UX Research \| research-repository (reuse-first: query before any new study; findings tagged product/persona/journey, linked to PRDs) C \· study-design (protocols, consent, sample discipline) C \· synthesis-discipline (findings → claims with confidence flags, never vibes) C \· voice-of-customer-intake (support tickets/reviews/NPS verbatims → repo, standing pipeline — Client Success boundary) C \· usability-testing M + jtbd-interviews M (candidates at build) \| · h2:team agents pods=\| \| **loom** \| PMF & Experimentation \| pmf-scorecard (Ellis survey cadence + retention-curve flatness, verdict to spec/marcus — 0.6-flagged rubric) C \· assumption-mapping (riskiest first) C \· experiment-discipline (cheapest falsifying test, pre-set decision rules, criteria frozen before running — proto's eval-first pattern, product-side) C \· experiment-registry (every verdict recorded, adopt-reject pattern — the fleet never unknowingly reruns a settled experiment) C \· lean-experimentation M (candidate at build) \| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Measurement** \| **metric** \| Product Analytics \| product-metrics-spec (event taxonomy + versioned activation/retention definitions — the single metric truth) C \· funnel-instrumentation (AARRR mapping, gap detection, cohort reads) C \· experiment-instrumentation (loom's measurement arm — no experiment without its instruments pre-verified) C \· metrics-governance (definition changes versioned + proposed, never silent; sync INTERFACE to the data layer and kai's dashboards — river binding deferred) C \· aarrr-framework M (candidate at build) \| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Monetization** \| **price** 🆕 \| Pricing & Packaging \| pricing-research (willingness-to-pay methods — van Westendorp/conjoint as 0.6-flagged rubrics until the pricing book lands) C \· packaging-tiers (feature-to-tier mapping, fence design, per-product config) C \· pricing-experiment-discipline (with loom's registry; revenue experiments get extra blast-radius rules) C \· price-change-governance (impact analysis; routes through board when locked commitments in scope; grandfathering discipline) C \| · h2:team agents pods=leader (identity holder). new catalog. agent custom skills; marketplace candidates confirmed playbook 4.1–4.4 build (search purpose, present sources, stop). Total: agents, ~21 custom skills marketplace adoptions. **spec's identity proposal:** archetype *evidence-first-discoverer* relentless about problem-before-solution, allergic feature-lists-as-strategy, treats "no" product decision reasons. Optional named inspiration (e.g. discovery-methodology figure) left operator; suggest archetype-only, matching meta's precedent. · h2:Cross-department boundaries (share, don't duplicate)=**spec quinn (Engineering):** acceptance criteria written testable quinn's gate spec owns WHAT passes, quinn owns WHETHER passed. Echo-confirmed handoff directions., **spec vista (Executive Office):** vista owns company roadmap; spec feeds per-product evidence receives priorities spec never publishes rival roadmap., **metric kai (Brand Studio):** kai owns brand/marketing/SEO analytics; metric owns in-product behavior. activation definition metric's; campaign attribution kai's. Shared reads cite owner's number., **metric river (future Data Analytics):** definitions sync stated interface (versioned definitions file), binding dept builds dangling pointer handled forge way, minus misfiling., **loom proto/forge (AI Agents):** one experiment discipline, different subjects loom tests PRODUCT hypotheses users; proto tests AGENT hypotheses cage; forge benchmarks MODELS. loom's registry mirrors scout's adopt-reject pattern., **ux Client Success (future):** voice-of-customer-intake consumes support exhaust; Client Success support relationship intake read-only their pipeline., **price board (Governance):** price changes touching locked commitments (price guarantees, grandfathering) gate board; price changes logged proposals (silent repricing trust incident). **price felix/Finance (future):** price sets price; finance owns margin/treasury math boundary stated now, bound later., **ux/loom Behavioral Science (future):** persuasion/bias frameworks (kahneman al.) dept's flags dependency, doesn't inline pop psychology., **All agents:** Fleet Charter binds (registered tools only, board-gated skill changes anneal); gauge scorecards agents like any others. · h2:7. Build order=**spec** (leader identity Evidence Gate law skills). **metric** (measurement before creation gauge's precedent; metric truth exist before outcomes read). **ux** (the evidence supply). **loom** (experiments consumes metric's instrumentation ux's evidence). **price** (monetization leans loom's registry metric's reads). **DEPARTMENT-WORKFLOW.md** (only after five). Cadence playbook: marketplace-search-first skill (candidates named hypotheses, adoptions scout's marketplace-skill-scouting runs searches exists), present sources, build, audit (`skill_audit.py` post-build standing), present.